modules.description: Provides session management operations including generating, retrieving, updating, and removing session data. Works with string-based keys, string values, and integer-based expiration periods. Used to handle session lifecycles in web applications, ensuring timely expiration and secure storage.

Provides functions to parse and generate HTTP cookies, including handling of attributes like domain, path, secure, and http-only. Works with strings and custom record types representing cookie properties. Enables session management in web applications by serializing and deserializing cookie data.

Manages session data through operations that generate, retrieve, update, and remove entries using string keys, string values, and integer expiration times. Sessions are stored and accessed via cookie-based mechanisms, supporting web application session lifecycle management. Functions include setting a session with a specified timeout and fetching session data by key. Example tasks include storing user authentication tokens and invalidating sessions after inactivity.
